<div><h3>HIST 238 - America, Russia, and the Cold War, 1917-1991 </h3>  <hr>This course will focus on the Russian-American rivalry at the center of world politics from the Bolshevik Revolution in 1917 through the collapse of the Soviet Union in 1991. Major topics include the escalating nuclear arms race, recurrent crises in Vietnam, Cuba and other parts of the Third World, and important personalities from Harry Truman and Josef Stalin to Ronald Reagan and Mikhail Gorbachev.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every year.<br><br></div>		</td>
